---
layout: base.njk
title: "Learning Paths â€” The Debate Guide"
description: "Curated reading paths for different goals: workplace persuasion, logic mastery, Socratic questioning, and more."
permalink: /learning-paths/
---
{% block styles %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ '/css/chapter.css' | url }}?v={{ build.timestamp }}">
<style>
/* Learning Paths Page Styles */
.paths-intro {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-lg);
    text-align: center;
}

.paths-intro p {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
}

.paths-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
}

.path-card {
    background: rgba(var(--color-white-rgb), 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-white-rgb), 0.1);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    transition: all 0.2s ease-out;
}

[data-theme="light"] .path-card {
    background: rgba(var(--color-black-rgb), 0.02);
    border-color: rgba(var(--color-black-rgb), 0.1);
}

.path-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(var(--color-gold-rgb), 0.03);
}

.path-card.featured {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(var(--color-gold-rgb), 0.05);
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
}

.path-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.path-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: rgba(var(--color-gold-rgb), 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-gold-rgb), 0.3);
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

.path-icon svg {
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    stroke: var(--accent);
    fill: none;
    stroke-width: 1.5;
}

.path-title-group {
    flex: 1;
}

.path-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
}

.path-time {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--accent);
}

.path-description {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

.path-chapters {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-white-rgb), 0.1);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
}

[data-theme="light"] .path-chapters {
    border-color: rgba(var(--color-black-rgb), 0.1);
}

.path-chapters-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
}

.path-chapter-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
}

.path-chapter-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
}

.path-chapter-item a {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
}

.path-chapter-item a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
}

.path-chapter-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    min-width: 1.5em;
}

.path-start {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    transition: all 0.2s ease-out;
}

.path-start:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--color-dark-bg);
}

.path-start svg {
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
}

.paths-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-white-rgb), 0.1);
}

[data-theme="light"] .paths-footer {
    border-color: rgba(var(--color-black-rgb), 0.1);
}

.paths-footer p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    color: var(--text-muted);
}

.paths-footer a {
    color: var(--accent);
}

@media (max-width: 720px) {
    .paths-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .path-card.featured {
        grid-column: 1;
    }
}
</style>
{% endblock %}

{# Page Hero #}
<section class="chapter-hero section-dark">
    {% include "sunburst.njk" %}
    <p class="chapter-part">Reference</p>
    <div class="chapter-number" style="opacity: 0.05;">&#9670;</div>
    <h1 class="chapter-title">LEARNING PATHS</h1>
    <p class="chapter-subtitle">Curated journeys through classical rhetoric</p>
</section>

<div class="deco-border"></div>

<section class="section section-dark">
    <article class="chapter-content" style="max-width: 960px;">

        <div class="paths-intro">
            <p>
                The Debate Guide is designed to be read sequentially, but sometimes you have a specific goal. These curated paths group chapters by theme, letting you focus on what matters most to you right now.
            </p>
        </div>

        {# Helper macro for chapter URL lookup #}
        {%- macro getChapterUrl(chapterNum) -%}
            {%- for part in chapters.parts -%}
                {%- for chapter in part.chapters -%}
                    {%- if chapter.number == chapterNum -%}
                        {{ '/chapters/' + part.id + '/chapter-' + (chapter.number | padZero) + '-' + chapter.slug + '/' | url }}
                    {%- endif -%}
                {%- endfor -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endmacro -%}

        {# Helper macro for chapter title lookup #}
        {%- macro getChapterTitle(chapterNum) -%}
            {%- for part in chapters.parts -%}
                {%- for chapter in part.chapters -%}
                    {%- if chapter.number == chapterNum -%}
                        {{ chapter.title }}
                    {%- endif -%}
                {%- endfor -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endmacro -%}

        {# Icon SVGs #}
        {%- macro pathIcon(icon) -%}
            {%- if icon == "scroll" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M4 4h16v16H4z"/><path d="M8 8h8M8 12h8M8 16h4"/></svg>
            {%- elif icon == "briefcase" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 7V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v2"/></svg>
            {%- elif icon == "target" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg>
            {%- elif icon == "question" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><circle cx="12" cy="17" r="0.5" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
            {%- elif icon == "globe" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M2 12h20M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg>
            {%- elif icon == "book" -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"/></svg>
            {%- else -%}
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
            {%- endif -%}
        {%- endmacro -%}

        <div class="paths-grid">
            {%- for path in paths.paths -%}
            <div class="path-card{% if path.id == 'complete-journey' %} featured{% endif %}">
                <div class="path-header">
                    <div class="path-icon">
                        {{ pathIcon(path.icon) }}
                    </div>
                    <div class="path-title-group">
                        <h2 class="path-title">{{ path.title }}</h2>
                        <span class="path-time">{{ path.time }}</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="path-description">{{ path.description }}</p>

                <div class="path-chapters">
                    <div class="path-chapters-label">{{ path.chapters | length }} Chapters</div>
                    <ul class="path-chapter-list">
                        {%- for chapterNum in path.chapters -%}
                        <li class="path-chapter-item">
                            <span class="path-chapter-number">{{ chapterNum }}.</span>
                            <a href="{{ getChapterUrl(chapterNum) | trim }}">{{ getChapterTitle(chapterNum) | trim }}</a>
                        </li>
                        {%- endfor -%}
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <a href="{{ getChapterUrl(path.chapters[0]) | trim }}" class="path-start">
                    Start Path
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                        <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
                    </svg>
                </a>
            </div>
            {%- endfor -%}
        </div>

        <div class="paths-footer">
            <p>
                All paths draw from the same twenty chapters. For the complete experience, start with <a href="{{ '/chapters/part-1/chapter-01-why-debate-matters/' | url }}">Chapter 1: Why Debate Matters</a>.
            </p>
        </div>

    </article>

    {# Navigation #}
    <nav class="chapter-nav">
        <a href="{{ '/' | url }}" class="chapter-nav-prev">
            <span class="chapter-nav-label">&larr; Back</span>
            <span class="chapter-nav-title">Table of Contents</span>
        </a>
        <div class="chapter-nav-contents">
            <a href="/">Contents</a>
        </div>
        <a href="{{ '/quick-tactics/' | url }}" class="chapter-nav-next">
            <span class="chapter-nav-label">Next &rarr;</span>
            <span class="chapter-nav-title">Quick Tactics</span>
        </a>
    </nav>
</section>

<div class="deco-border"></div>
